  "longBusinessSummary": "M. Dias Branco S.A. Ind\u00fastria e Com\u00e9rcio de Alimentos manufactures, distributes, and sells food products in Brazil. Its principal product categories are cookies and crackers, pasta, wheat flour and bran, and margarine and vegetable shortening; cakes, cake mixes, snacks and nuts, toasts, peanut butter, seasonings, chocolates, granola and grains, breads and wraps, sugar, and sweeteners. The company offers its products under the Adria, Aldente, Basilar, Bonsabor, Estrela, Fortaleza, Finna, Fit Food, Frontera, Isabela, Jasmine, Pel\u00e1gio, Pilar, Piraqu\u00ea, Predilleto, Richester, Salsito, Smart, Taste&Co, Treloso, Vitarella, Zabet, and Las Acacias brands. The company also offers refined oils and wheat milling services. It also exports its products. The company was founded in 1936 and is headquartered in Eus\u00e9bio, Brazil.",
